body_html:
@andrewharp , thanks a lot for your help!
I use the new version(actually, I add the inverse to Android kernel filegroups ), and this error disappears.

However, I meet some other errors:

06-06 15:26:10.871 16634-16634/jp.narr.tensorflowmnist E/native: tensorflow_jni.cc:262 Error during inference: Invalid argument: No OpKernel was registered to support Op 'Switch' with these attrs
                                                                      [[Node: incept5b/in4_conv1x1_55/batch_norm/cond/Switch = Switch[T=DT_BOOL](phase_train, phase_train)]]
06-06 15:26:10.871 16634-16634/jp.narr.tensorflowmnist A/libc: Fatal signal 11 (SIGSEGV), code 1, fault addr 0x10 in tid 16634 (tensorflowmnist)

It needs a op called Switch", do you know what that is?
Thanks.

body:
@andrewharp , thanks a lot for your help!
I use the new version(actually, I add the inverse to Android kernel filegroups ), and this error disappears.

However, I meet some other errors:

```
06-06 15:26:10.871 16634-16634/jp.narr.tensorflowmnist E/native: tensorflow_jni.cc:262 Error during inference: Invalid argument: No OpKernel was registered to support Op 'Switch' with these attrs
                                                                      [[Node: incept5b/in4_conv1x1_55/batch_norm/cond/Switch = Switch[T=DT_BOOL](phase_train, phase_train)]]
06-06 15:26:10.871 16634-16634/jp.narr.tensorflowmnist A/libc: Fatal signal 11 (SIGSEGV), code 1, fault addr 0x10 in tid 16634 (tensorflowmnist)
```

It needs a op called Switch", do you know what that is?
Thanks.
